---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Manifesto"
  description="The standards FeedForwardClub tries to keep as the room grows."
  ogType="article"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Manifesto</span>
      <h1>What we <em class="accent">protect</em> as we grow.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Not rules. Not branding copy. Just the standards that keep the room
        useful when it gets bigger and reputation starts crowding out signal.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <section class="section manifesto">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Culture</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Four standards for the room.</h2>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">I.</span>
          <h3>Signal over status.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          The world already over-rewards people who have won before. Capital
          follows capital. Attention follows attention. The polished founder
          gets heard before the unknown one with the better instinct.
        </p>
        <p>
          We are not here to replay that. The room should stay weighted toward
          people with more to prove than to protect:
          <strong>roughly 60% early builders and 40% established ones</strong>.
          If that flips, the room starts teaching performance instead of
          judgment.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">II.</span>
          <h3>Respect is non-negotiable.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          No racism. No sexism. No gatekeeping. No hiding contempt inside
          "banter" or "just being honest." If someone makes the room smaller
          for other people, they are the problem.
        </p>
        <p>
          Past work matters. It just does not buy immunity here. We care more
          about what you are obsessed with, what truth you see early, and who
          your work is actually for.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">III.</span>
          <h3>Be useful, not theatrical.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          Blunt is fine. Cruel is lazy. Give the kind of feedback that helps
          this person make a better move next week, not the kind that makes you
          sound superior for thirty seconds.
        </p>
        <p>
          The goal is not to win the room. The goal is to leave someone
          clearer, sharper, and more capable than when they walked in.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header>
          <span class="num">IV.</span>
          <h3>Responsibility, not rank.</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          This club does not need a social ladder. It does need people who take
          responsibility for the room while the culture is still fragile.
        </p>
        <p>
          A steward curates the room, protects the standard, and calls out
          drift. That is stewardship, not status. If the culture gets strong
          enough to do that on its own, the role should shrink, rotate, or
          disappear.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p class="sign">— FeedForwardClub</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="rule" />
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
  .hero {
    padding: clamp(72px, 10vw, 140px) 0 clamp(32px, 5vw, 64px);

    .lede { max-width: 680px; margin-top: 16px; }
    h1 em.accent { font-style: italic; color: $accent; }
  }

  .manifesto .container { max-width: 760px; }

  .section-title { margin-bottom: 24px; }

  .entry {
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid $rule;

    &:last-of-type { border-bottom: 0; }

    header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 12px 16px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    @media (max-width: $bp-sm) {
      header {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }
    }

    .num {
      font-family: $font-serif;
      font-size: 26px;
      color: $accent;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    h3 { margin: 0; font-size: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 28px); }

    p {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: $ink-soft;
    }
  }

  .sign {
    font-family: $font-serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: $ink;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }
</style>
